^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|This was really excellent bidding and nicely played. Very intricate and nice auction. Let us discuss the control bidding sequence. First of all, the 2S bid initially, that is asking about a NT stopper. However, it could also be a slam try in clubs, depending on Yvon's follow up. In this case, since Yvon pulled 2N to 3C, that said the 2S was not a stopper ask, but a slam try in clubs. With a 7 card clubs suit, and very nice controls, Linda wants to accept slam, so should control bid.|
