^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Well this was a hand where, in hindsight, I think my opening bid was wrong. Normally, I don't like to open 1N with 2 doubletons. I like my 1N openers to be 4-3-3-3 4-4-3-2 or 5-3-3-2. But, on this hand, I have a hard rebid over 1H or 1S. 2C is too weak, 3C is too strong given my suit, which is ok but not great, and 1N is also a bit weak. So, if I open 1N, it gives partner a better idea of what I have. It is a slight lie, but not a bad one. Not sure how we do in 3N on a diamond lead. I think it makes because hearts behave very nicely. So, had I opened 1N, we get to 3N or 4H. 4H is even easier.|
