HT|S|CP|5|AT|^B@2^Y@3I am sure you noticed that Hands A-27 and A-28 are indeed the same hand. |CP||AT|The difference is in the auction. In A-27, the auction goes 1@H-1@S-4@C, which devalues the 1@S bidder's hand quite a bit, due to the club points. In A-28, the auction goes 1@H-1@S-4@D, which improves the value of the 1@S bidder's hand quite a bit, since he has only small diamonds (the J is not worth much). So, in A-27, the 1@S bidder should simply close out in game by bidding 4@S. In A-28, the 1S bidder should look for slam. He can do that by either bidding 4@H (control bid), or jumping right to 4N, since he knows that all suits are controlled (partner has diamonds controlled, and he has hearts and clubs controlled)|
